name: Hollar's Map of Lancashire (c.1650s)
description: Wenceslaus Hollar's map of Lancashire. Hollar was a Bohemian etcher who worked extensively in England.
notes:
Wenceslaus Hollar (1607-1677), Bohemian-born etcher.
Produced maps and views across England.
Lancashire map from his English county series.
Smaller format than Saxton/Speed but finely engraved.
Hollar is best known for his panoramic view of London before the Great Fire.
